If value of Time of ComingHome property not met the range condition, OutOfRangemessage is send in response. Otherwise, when value of Time of ComingHome property is in range, it is verified if received value of Time parameter differs from value stored in el_NvM_Perso_Params structure and verified the possibility to do modifications by the user by checking coding stored in el_Coding_Values structure. When no new value of Time parameter was received and/or State parameter cannot be modified by the user, invalid argument message is send in response. In oposite case, base on possible type of modification, new values of peronalized parameters (time, state and type of CommingHome) are stored in el_NvM_Perso_Params together with reseted isDefault flag and isDirty flag set to PSO_DIRTYSTATE_DIRTY. Values of Time and State parameters are provided to ExteriorLight module and status message is send in response.
